plot_rt: The intricacies of relationships in a modern world, where trust and loyalty are tested through temptation and doubt.

Mariachi (Antonio Banderas) plunges headfirst into the dark border underworld when he follows a trail of blood to the last of the infamous Mexican drug lords, Bucho (Joaquim de Almeida), for an action-packed, bullet-riddled showdown. With the help of his best friend (Steve Buscemi) and a beautiful bookstore owner (Salma Hayek), the Mariachi tracks Bucho, takes on his army of desperados, and leaves a trail of blood of his own.
With his sister seriously ill and his family struggling to pay the bills, a boy seeks to help his loved ones by writing a letter asking for divine help.
Best friends Angela and Lexi run away after committing a crime. Soon, their seemingly quiet life becomes messy when a man enters the picture.

plot_rt: A dysfunctional couple, Lars (Aksel Hennie) and Lisa (Noomi Rapace), head to a remote cabin under the guise of reconnecting, but each has intentions to kill the other. Before they can carry out their plans, unexpected visitors arrive and they are faced with a greater danger.

New to Los Angeles, rideshare driver Clare picks up Carl from a home deep in the Hollywood Hills. What begins as a routine ride turns into Clare’s worst nightmare: a twelve-hour fight for survival through the city’s seedy underbelly. Carl is not the passenger Clare thought he was, and Clare is not easy prey.
Psychiatrist Carrie Williams becomes interested in a mysterious client who begins to reveal a secret past.

plot_rt: An allegorical day-in-the-life adventure lived through the eyes of a naïve, determined young girl in search of her missing homework assignment, while the pressures of the adult world threaten her and her rural mountain village in Pakistan.
A radio hoax makes an agoraphobic young woman believe the world is ending.
